    <h3 class="title"><a href="/what-do-i-want-5d-mark-3-next-generation-digital-slr#comment-13197" class="active">DNG</a></h3>    <div class="submitted">Submitted by <a href="http://www.astro.multivax.de:8000/helbig/helbig.html" rel="nofollow">Phillip Helbig</a> (not verified) on Fri, 2011-11-18 13:06.</div>
    <div class="content"><p>I agree with both statements above.  For the pros, or those who take photography as seriously as the pros, Canon or Nikon is probably the way to go, for the reasons you mention.  However, for someone like me, who used a conventional SLR and a few lenses for decades and waited until DSLRs were good enough before switching, and plans to use this camera and at most a few lenses in the next, say, 10 years, I think one should seriously consider Pentax.</p>
<p>Pentax also supports DNG as well as their own raw format (and of course JPEG).  I save both raw and JPEG on the card.</p>
<p>What do you think of DNG, both in terms of technical advantages/disadvantages and in terms of a future-proof standard (assuming it is)?  Rune stones are still readable, 10-inch diskettes probably aren't in many cases.</p>
</div>
