    <h3 class="title"><a href="/what-do-i-want-5d-mark-3-next-generation-digital-slr#comment-13201" class="active">Jpeg mostly</a></h3>    <div class="submitted">Submitted by <a href="/user/brad" title="View user profile." rel="nofollow">brad</a> on Sat, 2011-11-19 12:06.</div>
    <div class="content"><p>I shoot either jpeg or raw+jpeg when in a setting of unusual light or contrast that might need raw.  The truth is that raw is a pain to work with, so I use raw+jpg an use the jpegs for browsing, organizing and experiments and go to the raw if I need it.   I archive as shot, I never change (other than to rotate or delete complete losers) my original files.</p>
</div>
